OL,3,COfficial says NIO should have offered
OL,4,CRosemary Nelson protection 'in
OL,5,Chindsight'
OL,7,FShortly before her killing the NIO
OL,8,Foffered protection to two of her
OL,9,Fclients, Portadown councillors
OL,10,FBreandan McCionnaith and Joe Duffy,
OL,11,Fwho were campaigning against Orange
OL,12,FOrder demands to march on Garvaghy
OL,13,FRoad.
OL,15,FHowever, the NIO decided not to offer
OL,16,Fthe same to Mrs Nelson because she had
OL,17,Fnot sought it, she was not a member of
OL,18,Fthe Garvaghy Road residents'
OL,19,Fcoalition, and she was not a
OL,20,Fcouncillor.
