OL,7,FBefore her death, the Chief Constable
OL,8,Fwas unhappy that a United Nations'
OL,9,Fspecial rapporteur's report claimed
OL,10,Fthat Mr Flanagan believed "that
OL,11,Fsolicitors may in fact be working for
OL,12,Fparamilitaries", though no supporting
OL,13,Fevidence was given.
OL,15,FUnhappy that such words were
OL,16,Fattributed to him, he sought their
OL,17,Fremoval and "said that if the comments
OL,18,Fwere kept in the report there may be a
OL,19,Fdanger to life of Rosemary Nelson from
OL,20,Floyalist paramilitaries".
