OL,3,COfficial says NIO should have offered
OL,4,CRosemary Nelson protection 'in
OL,5,Chindsight'
OL,7,FIt said it believed the leaking of
OL,8,Fpolice intelligence "increased the
OL,9,Fdanger to Rosemary Nelson's life",
OL,10,Fwhile threats made against the
OL,11,Fsolicitor by officers, "had the
OL,12,Fsubsequent effect of legitimising her
OL,13,Fas a target in the eyes of loyalist
OL,14,Fterrorists".
OL,16,FThe report catalogued failures by the
OL,17,FRoyal Ulster Constabulary (RUC) and
OL,18,Fthe Northern Ireland Office (NIO)
OL,19,Fwhich resulted in a failure to warn
OL,20,FMrs Nelson of the danger she faced or
OL,21,Fto offer her adequate protection.
